Let's look at some numbers... in 6 minutes from INC, I've been able to do 74.9k damage without manaburning, but using quite a lot of mana even with horse/bard/enc/dru/aaflappy2/mc1/ft15/etc. I think the final figure after 10 minutes was 30% mana left, 1 rod and HoD used. And total damage after 10 minutes was 152k damage done or 253dps.<br>
<br>
So, I wouldn't be able to push that damage if I MB'd for 19k or say 20k in the beginning. Not even close. And if I was doing that damage for the first 6 minutes, I wouldn't do 20k burn at six minute marker.<br>
<br>
If I burn first, and have 100 mana / tick regen, that equals to 2x ADoI in 18 seconds (except 2x ADoI takes 26s but I give it to benefit the MB calc). Wich means I can cast 40 of those from 0 to 6 minutes, plus say 3 from HoD/Rod but that makes some ticks lost. Now, an ADoI makes about 1700 damage on average, so those 43 would be about 73k. Add the 20k and you get 93k for me at 6 minute marker... but the remaining 4 minutes would be on still the same slow nuking rythm... adding about 27 more nukes or 46k damage... totalling to 139k damage from the wizard who burned first. Or... 232dps.<br>
<br>
Now, I'm no math wizard but even with new MB, it looks like I shouldn't use the MB. And if the MB result was based on mana left, then the 5th or 6th wizard shouldn't either... even SoM or AT or SoS should be better choice for 6s cast at that time. I might've error in calculations with the MB, if so, someone please correct me.<br>
<br>
On a shorter fight, maybe the first or 2nd MB would be beneficial, but spells like SoS doing easily 5-6.5k damage per nuke, I'm a bit doubtful at that. Also when you take into account that at 3 minute marker no wizard should be full of mana, because the dps lost wouldn't be made up for by MB.<br>
<br>
